{"titre":"Los Angeles World Cup stadium workers threaten strike over ICE deployment","auteur":"Al Jazeera","date_publication":"2026-05-19 07:37:08","categorie":"sports","contenu":"Workers represented by a local union say ICE presence would create a climate of fear during the FIFA World Cup 2026. Save Share Workers at the SoFi Stadium in Los Angeles have decided to go on strike if federal immigration enforcement agents are deployed at the venue when it hosts FIFA World Cup matches in June and July. The UNITE HERE Local 11 ŌĆō a labour union representing some 2,000 hospitality employees ŌĆō on Monday demanded federal guarantees that Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) would not be used during the matches scheduled at the stadium.     The venue, which will be known as the Los Angeles Stadium during the tournament, will host eight World Cup games, including the opening fixture for the United States on June 12. Workers at the worldŌĆÖs most expensive sports arena say the ICE presence would create a climate of fear for themselves and for fans. ŌĆ£ICE should have no role in these games,ŌĆØ said Isaac Martinez, a stadium cook, at a protest outside the venue. ŌĆ£We do not want to live in fear coming to work, or fear being detained going home.ŌĆØ ŌĆ£If we do not reach an agreement, my colleagues and I are ready to strike,ŌĆØ Martinez added, speaking on behalf of a workforce composed largely of food and beverage concession staff. ICE has led the charge in President Donald TrumpŌĆÖs immigration crackdown. Human rights groups have condemned the agency for its conduct during raids in several US cities, including Los Angeles last year. In early 2026, ICE agents fatally shot two American protesters in Minneapolis. Workers on Monday also raised alarms over FIFAŌĆÖs accreditation process, which requires employees to submit personal data before the tournament, which runs from June 11 to July 19 across the US, Canada and Mexico. ŌĆ£We ask FIFA not to share our information with ICE agencies, foreign countries, or intelligence services,ŌĆØ worker Yolanda Fierro said. Protesters carrying plastic balls and signs reading ŌĆ£Kick ICE Out of the World CupŌĆØ drew support from Tom Steyer, a Democratic candidate in CaliforniaŌĆÖs gubernatorial race. ICEŌĆÖs mandate is border control, the financier-turned-politician said. ŌĆ£Can anyone explain what that has to do with the World Cup? Nothing,ŌĆØ Steyer said. ŌĆ£How is it possible that this is the agency that is going to be here when we know in fact theyŌĆÖre an absolute threat, a lawless threat, to workers in California?ŌĆØ             Follow Al Jazeera English:","source":"Al Jazeera","url":"https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/5/19/los-angeles-world-cup-stadium-workers-threaten-strike-over-ice-deployment","kafka_timestamp":"2026-05-19T09:52:47.240Z","ingestion_time":"2026-05-19T09:53:00.008Z"}
