{"titre":"Iran war day 81: Trump delays attack; Tehran says wonŌĆÖt ŌĆśsurrenderŌĆÖ","auteur":"Elizabeth Melimopoulos","date_publication":"2026-05-19 07:26:51","categorie":"news","contenu":"The US president says he held off a scheduled attack on Iran after pressure from Gulf allies as renewed talks gain momentum amid tensions. Save Share United States President Donald Trump saidhe postponed a planned attackon Iran after requests from the leaders of Qatar, Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates, adding that ŌĆ£serious negotiations are now taking placeŌĆØ behind the scenes. The comments suggest renewed diplomatic efforts are under way amid weeks of escalating tensions between Washington and Tehran. Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian defended TehranŌĆÖsparticipation in talkswhile rejecting suggestions that the country was backing down under pressure. ŌĆ£Dialogue does not mean surrender,ŌĆØ he said, adding that Iran had entered negotiations ŌĆ£with dignity, authority, and the preservation of the nationŌĆÖs rightsŌĆØ. Meanwhile, there is no letup in Israeli attacks on Lebanon as the death toll crossed 3,000, with at least seven people reported killed on Monday, according to local reports, despite a US-brokered extension of the ŌĆ£ceasefireŌĆØ. Here is what we know:                Follow Al Jazeera English:","source":"Al Jazeera","url":"https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/5/19/iran-war-day-81-trump-delays-attack-tehran-says-wont-surrender","kafka_timestamp":"2026-05-19T09:52:48.593Z","ingestion_time":"2026-05-19T09:53:00.008Z"}
